The paper deals with weighted finite automata (WFA) and their relationship to rational series, which are functions from strings to real numbers. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) category. The paper also discusses the use of Hankel matrices in the theory of minimal WFA, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper's focus on the singular value decomposition (SVD) and its application to WFA suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT) categories. Finally, the paper's algorithm for constructing approximate minimizations of a given WFA could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
